    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-04-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-04-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="302" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d302">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 904.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-04-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 7, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch of the 23d of March, No.
                            628, has been received, and your proceedings therein related in regard
                            to the supposed outfit of the screw steamer Amphion are approved. The
                            frank explanations which Earl Russell so properly made upon that subject
                            are appreciated by this government. I am, sir, your obedient
                            servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">C. F. Adams</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
